Hello Jeff and Gagan,

Gagan called in today requesting VPN assistance. I want to confirm in writi=
ng =97 consistent with my April 3, 2026 email on access, transition coordin=
ation, and outstanding invoices =97 why Technijian is unable to act on this=
 request, what has continued to change in the environment since that email,=
 and what we need from Boston Group to resume support through the April 30,=
 2026 termination date.

Documented access obstructions =97 sequence of events:

  1.  Night of March 31, 2026 =97 Tech Heights personnel worked in the envi=
ronment after hours. The ESXi host password was changed without notice to T=
echnijian, locking us out of the virtualization layer. Reported to you in w=
riting on April 1, 2026 at 9:28 AM (Helpdesk email, Rishad Samad).
  2.  April 1, 2026 =97 BST-HQ-AD-01 Active Directory server went offline. =
Technijian offered to dispatch an engineer (Rishad) onsite the same day to =
restore service. That offer was declined at 11:29 AM ("No thank you. Let's =
just resolve this and move on.").
  3.  April 2, 2026 (evening) =96 April 3, 2026 =97 BST-HQ-AD-02 also went =
offline. CrowdStrike detected and blocked an unauthorized attempt to elevat=
e a new account to the Domain Admins group. Reported to you in writing on A=
pril 3, 2026 at 2:32 AM (Rishad Mohamed, "RE: Urgent: Suspicious Activity D=
etected on BST-HQ-AD-02").
  4.  April 3, 2026 =97 Technijian's remote management tools were removed, =
our administrative access account was disabled, and RDP access to the AD se=
rvers was revoked. Documented in my April 3, 2026 email (Ed Susolik cc'd) a=
sking Boston Group to confirm Tech Heights as the primary administrator goi=
ng forward and to identify authorized Tech Heights recipients for credentia=
ls.
  5.  Since April 3, 2026 =97 Additional environmental changes have been ob=
served by our engineers, including:
     *   Default gateway changed from 10.1.1.254 to 10.1.1.1 and the previo=
us firewall replaced. Technijian has no credentials on the current gateway =
or firewall.
     *   Technijian monitoring and management agents have been removed from=
 BST endpoints and servers.
     *   Domain controllers continue to be inaccessible to Technijian.

Result for today's VPN request: Without credentials to the current firewall=
/gateway, the current domain controllers, or the current hypervisor, Techni=
jian cannot diagnose or remediate the reported VPN issue. Our engineer dire=
cted Gagan to contact Tech Heights, since Tech Heights currently holds the =
operational credentials. This email confirms that direction in writing.

Our position through April 30, 2026:

  *   Technijian remains contractually willing to provide support through t=
he termination date per Section 4.05 of the signed agreement. Our offer of =
April 1 (onsite dispatch) and April 3 (coordinated access restoration) both=
 remain available.
  *   We cannot provide support without administrative access. If Boston Gr=
oup directs Tech Heights to (a) restore the ESXi host credentials, (b) rest=
ore a Technijian administrative account on the current domain controllers, =
(c) provide read/admin credentials on the current firewall/gateway, and (d)=
 reinstate our monitoring and management agents, we will resume normal supp=
ort response immediately.
  *   Otherwise, please direct all active support requests to Tech Heights,=
 which currently holds the operational credentials for the BST environment.

Reservation of rights:

Nothing in this email waives, releases, or limits any claim Technijian may =
